A variety of soft calls given by three Red-breasted Nuthatches (Sitta canadensis) in between significantly louder songs of Pine Warbler (Setophaga pinus). I archived this recording primarily because of the harsh, raspy call audible at 0:16, 0:21, and 0:48 of the recording; this is not a call that I am familiar with from this species. These three birds were vocalizing as they chased each other high up in a red pine, but I do not know the exact behavioral context of any of the calls in this recording.
